  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If the implementation contract has a a `require` statement, the textual error message mentioned there will not be propagated up. This means that if a user calls a function on the proxy contract, they will not get the human-readable error message returned by the implementation.\r\n\r\nA suggestion is to wrap the delegate call similar to this [StackOverflow thread](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/69133/forward-revert-message-from-low-level-solidity-call).\r\n",
